# Mom Care Platform Backend - Project Structure

## Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Ktor (Kotlin)
- **Database**: MongoDB with KMongo
- **Authentication**: JWT with refresh tokens
- **Serialization**: Gson (preferred), avoid kotlinx.serialization
- **Dependency Injection**: Koin
- **Testing**: Bash scripts with curl and jq
- **Documentation**: OpenAPI/Swagger, Postman

## File Structure
```
src/main/kotlin/
├── Application.kt                 # Main application entry point
├── auth/                         # Authentication & authorization
│   ├── AuthAnnotations.kt
│   └── AuthInterceptor.kt
├── data/
│   ├── models/                   # Data models
│   ├── requests/                 # Request DTOs
│   ├── responses/                # Response DTOs
│   └── repository/               # Data access layer
├── di/                          # Dependency injection (Koin)
│   └── MainModule.kt
├── routes/                      # API route definitions
│   ├── admin/                   # Admin-only routes
│   ├── auth/                    # Authentication routes
│   ├── doctor/                  # Doctor routes
│   └── mom/                     # Mom routes
├── service/                     # Business logic layer
│   ├── auth/
│   ├── doctor/
│   └── mom/
└── util/                        # Utility functions
```

## Key Files
- [Application.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/Application.kt) - Main application entry point
- [Routing.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/Routing.kt) - Route configuration
- [MainModule.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/di/MainModule.kt) - Dependency injection setup
- [AuthInterceptor.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/auth/AuthInterceptor.kt) - Authentication interceptors
